cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.DC

The paper discusses multimedia streaming to mobile devices, which falls under the category of mobile computing and networking. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of streaming techniques on quality of experience and energy consumption, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves active measurements and analysis, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
